QUETTA: King Salman Humanitarian Aid and Relief Center distributed Sunday 3,950 winter bags to the needy people in Kalat and Quetta districts of Balochistan province, Pakistan, benefitting 27,650 people.
Recently, the center signed a joint memorandum of cooperation with the General Authority for Awqaf in Riyadh.
The agreement aims to establish an endowment fund for humanitarian, relief and charitable work.  Under the terms of the agreement, both parties will work to identify and detail the nature of the key roles within the action plan, including the fund’s system and its legal, regulatory, operational and financial frameworks.  
A report of the results will also be made three months after the memorandum is signed in order to achieve its objectives. 